(#### Q3 Answer) Tj
T*
(Search path:) Tj
T*
(1. BM25 lexical scores.) Tj
T*
(2. FAISS semantic scores for top `search_k`.) Tj
T*
(3. Min-max normalize each score vector.) Tj
T*
(4. Weighted sum with configured lexical/semantic weights.) Tj
T*
(5. Candidate selection via `argpartition`, then sorted tie-break using combined -> lexical ->) Tj
T*
(semantic.) Tj
T*
(Instability can happen when many normalized scores collapse to near-equal values \(especially with) Tj
T*
(sparse token overlap or low-variance vectors\), causing tie-heavy ranking dependence on secondary) Tj
T*
(sort fields.) Tj
T*
(Evidence: `src/ask_my_docs/retrieval/hybrid.py:340-369`, config) Tj
T*
(`src/ask_my_docs/settings.py:26-27`.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(#### Q4 Answer) Tj
T*
(Gate design enforces two layers:) Tj
T*
(- Absolute minima/maxima \(`min_answer_f1`, `max_latency_p95_ms`, etc.\).) Tj
T*
(- Relative baseline drift caps \(`max_answer_f1_drop`, etc.\) when baseline exists.) Tj
T*
(In CI, this blocks regressions after candidate metrics are computed. Baseline validity assumption) Tj
T*
(is crucial: stale or poor baseline weakens governance. The CLI also validates baseline payload has) Tj
T*
(`aggregate`.) Tj
T*
(Evidence: `configs/regression_thresholds.yaml:1-11`,) Tj
T*
(`src/ask_my_docs/evaluation/gating.py:52-124`, `src/ask_my_docs/cli.py:244-257`,) Tj
