(`.github/workflows/ci.yml:38-49`.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(#### Q5 Answer) Tj
T*
(Compatibility guards include:) Tj
T*
(- chunk/embedding row count alignment.) Tj
T*
(- embedding dimensional consistency across config, embeddings, and FAISS index.) Tj
T*
(- optional manifest consistency checks \(`chunk_count`, `embedding_dim`\).) Tj
T*
(These checks fail early with explicit `ValueError` messages, and tests verify mismatch handling.) Tj
T*
(Evidence: `src/ask_my_docs/retrieval/hybrid.py:130-172,238-307`, `tests/test_retrieval.py:38`.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(#### Scenario 1 Answer \(DB latency triples\)) Tj
T*
(Keep architecture, optimize internals:) Tj
T*
(1. Confirm bottleneck split between write path \(`record`\) and read path \(`summarize`\) using) Tj
T*
(span-level and DB-level timings.) Tj
T*
(2. Preserve current upsert semantics \(`ON CONFLICT\(request_id\)`\) to maintain idempotent request) Tj
T*
(row behavior.) Tj
T*
(3. Add DB maintenance and possibly partitioning/rollup strategy while keeping) Tj
T*
(`rag_request_metrics` contract stable.) Tj
T*
(4. For summary-heavy workloads, materialize rolling aggregates and keep existing `summarize` API) Tj
T*
(unchanged.) Tj
